content.text:
- **Therapeutic Targeting of CDK12/CDK13 in Triple-Negative Breast Cancer (PubMed)**
  - URL: `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/`
  - Direct quotes:
    - “Here we report the development of **SR-4835**, a highly selective dual inhibitor of **CDK12** and **CDK13**, which disables **triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC)** cells.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/))

- **Discovery of a Highly Potent and Selective Dual PROTAC Degrader of CDK12 and CDK13 (PubMed)**
  - URL: `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35938508/`
  - Direct quotes:
    - “dual **CDK12/13** degraders by employing the **proteolysis-targeting chimera (PROTAC)** technology.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35938508/))
    - “The optimal compound **7f** effectively degraded **CDK12** and **CDK13**” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35938508/))
    - “**7f** markedly inhibited proliferation of multiple **TNBC** cell lines” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35938508/))

- **Noncovalent CDK12/13 dual inhibitors-based PROTACs degrade CDK12-Cyclin K complex and induce synthetic lethality with PARP inhibitor (PubMed)**
  - URL: `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/`
  - Direct quotes:
    - “we have synthesized a potent **PROTAC** degrader **PP-C8** based on the noncovalent dual inhibitors of **CDK12/13**” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))
    - “**PP-C8** demonstrates profound synergistic antiproliferative effects with **PARP inhibitor** in **triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC)**.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))

- **Discovery of a molecular glue promoting CDK12-DDB1 interaction to trigger cyclin K degradation (PubMed)**
  - URL: `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32804079/`
  - Direct quotes:
    - “we report a new molecular glue **HQ461** discovered by high-throughput screening.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32804079/))
    - “**HQ461** acts by promoting an interaction between **CDK12** and **DDB1-CUL4-RBX1** E3 ubiquitin ligase” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32804079/))
    - “A provisional patent application (**PCT/CN2020/095482**) has been filed for the application of **HQ461**” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32804079/))

- **Dual-site molecular glues for enhancing protein-protein interactions of the CDK12-DDB1 complex (PubMed)**
  - URL: `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39090085/`
  - Direct quotes:
    - “This exploration leads to the creation of **LL-K12-18**, a dual-site molecular glue” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39090085/))
    - “potency improvements in **MDA-MB-231** (88-fold) and **MDA-MB-468** cells (307-fold) when compared to its precursor compound **SR-4835**.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39090085/))

- **THZ531 | CDK12/13 inhibitor | Axon 3402 | Axon Medchem**
  - URL: `https://www.axonmedchem.com/3402-thz531`
  - Direct quotes:
    - “**THZ531** is a first-in-class, potent, selective, covalent inhibitor of **CDK12** and **CDK13** with IC50 values of 158 nM and 69 nM, respectively.” ([axonmedchem.com](https://www.axonmedchem.com/3402-thz531))
    - “CAS:  1702809-17-3” ([axonmedchem.com](https://www.axonmedchem.com/3402-thz531))

- **LL-K12-18 | CDK12-DDB1enhancer,Cyclin K degrader | Axon 4281 | Axon Medchem**
  - URL: `https://www.axonmedchem.com/4281-ll-k12-18`
  - Direct quotes:
    - “**CAS:  3081311-94-3**” ([axonmedchem.com](https://www.axonmedchem.com/4281-ll-k12-18))
    - “The dual-site molecular glue **LL-K12-18** is an enhancer of **CDK12-DDB1** protein interaction and a potent degrader of cyclin K” ([axonmedchem.com](https://www.axonmedchem.com/4281-ll-k12-18))

- **Carrick Therapeutics Announces First Patient Dosed in Phase 1 Clinical Trial of CT7439 (CDK12/13 Inhibitor) (Carrick Therapeutics press release)**
  - URL: `https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/investors/news-events/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase`
  - Direct quotes:
    - “**CT7439**, a novel cyclin dependent kinase 12/13 (**CDK12/13**) inhibitor / **Cyclin-K glue-degrader**.” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/investors/news-events/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase))
    - “under study ID: **NCT06600789**.” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/investors/news-events/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase))
    - “including ovarian, breast and Ewing's Sarcoma.” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/investors/news-events/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase))

- **A Modular Phase 1/2 Study with CT7439 in Participants with Solid Malignancies (CareAcross; trial listing w/ locations)**
  - URL: `https://www.careacross.com/clinical-trials/trial/NCT06600789`
  - Direct quotes:
    - “NCT ID:  **NCT06600789**” ([careacross.com](https://www.careacross.com/clinical-trials/trial/NCT06600789?utm_source=openai))
    - “Intervention name:  **CT7439 Capsules (0.5 mg, 1mg, 3mg)**” ([careacross.com](https://www.careacross.com/clinical-trials/trial/NCT06600789))
    - “Country: **United States**” ([careacross.com](https://www.careacross.com/clinical-trials/trial/NCT06600789?utm_source=openai))
